e=Scarlett Johansson Lands $15 Million Payday for Black Widow Movie|last1=Siegel|first1=Tatiana|last2=Kit|first2=Borys|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=October 11, 2018|accessdate=October 11, 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181011163221/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/black-widow-movie-scarlett-johansson-lands-15-million-payday-1151328|archivedate=October 11, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://marvelcinematicuniverse.fandom.com/wiki/Black_Widow Black Widow] at Marvel Cinematic Universe Wiki\n* {{Marveldatabase|Natalia Romanoff (Earth-199999)|Marvel Cinematic Universe Black Widow}}\n* [https://www.marvel.com/characters/black-widow-natasha-romanoff/on-screen Black Widow (Natasha Romanoff) Biography] - Marvel Cinematic Universe (MCU) - Marvel Studios Official Web Site\n\n{{Marvel Cinematic Universe}}\n{{Black Widow (Marvel Comics)}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Romanoff, Natasha (Marvel Cinematic Universe)}}\n[[Category:Black Widow (Marvel Comics)]]\n[[Category:Female characters in film]]\n[[Category:Fictional American people of Russian descent]]\n[[Category:Fictional KGB agents]]\n[[Category:Fictional Soviet people]]\n[[Category:Fictional defectors]]\n[[Category:Fictional female assassins]]\n[[Category:Fictional female martial artists]]\n[[Category:Fictional female secret agents and spies]]\n[[Category:Fictional immigrants to the United States]]\n[[Category:Fictional orphans]]\n[[Category:Fictional outlaws]]\n[[Category:Fictional vigilantes]]\n[[Category:Fictional women soldiers and warriors]]\n[[Category:Film characters introduced in 2010]]\n[[Category:Marvel Cinematic Universe characters]]\n[[Category:Russian superheroes]]\n[[Category:S.H.I.E.L.D. agents]]\n[[Category:Superhero film characters]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2019}}\n{{short description| character in the Marvel Cinematic Universe}}\n{{Infobox character\n| color              = #AF181F\n| name               = Natasha Romanoff\n| franchise          = [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]]\n| image              = Scarlett Johansson as Black Widow.jpg\n| image_upright      = \n| caption            = [[Scarlett Johansson]] as Natasha Romanoff in ''[[Iron Man 2]]''\n| first_major        = \n| first_date         = \n| creator            = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Stan Lee]]\n* [[Don Rico]]\n* [[Don Heck]]\n}}\n| adapted_by         = \n| portrayer          = [[Scarlett Johansson]]\n| full_name          = Natalia Alianovna Romanoff\n| alias              = \n| occupation         = \n| family             = \n| spouse             = \n| children           = \n| affiliation        = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Avengers (comics)|Avengers]]\n* [[Red Room (comics)|The Black Widow Program]]\n* [[Clint Barton (Marvel Cinematic Universe)|Hawkeye (Clint Barton)]]\n* [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]]\n* [[S.T.R.I.K.E.]]\n}}\n| nationality        = Russian\n| series             = \n| alt                = \n| first              = ''[[Iron Man 2]]'' (2010)\n| last               = ''[[Black Widow (2020 film)|Black Widow]]'' (2020)\n| based_on           = \n| voice              = \n| origin             = \n| home               = \n}}\n'''Natasha Romanoff''' is a [[character (arts)|fictional character]] portrayed by [[Scarlett Johansson]] in the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]] (MCU) [[film franchise]]\u2014based on the [[Marvel Comics]] [[Black Widow (Natasha Romanova)|character of the same name]]\u2014sometimes known by her [[alter ego]], '''Black Widow'''. Romanoff is a spy and an expert hand-to-hand combatant, trained in the [[Red Room (comics)|Red Room]] from childhood. She eventually becomes part of the counter-terrorism agency [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]] (Strategic Homeland Intervention Enforcement and Logistics Division), through which the character was introduced to the franchise in ''[[Iron Man 2]]'', and then of the Avengers, defending her teammates and the Earth against various threats. The character will headline her own film, ''[[Black Widow (2020 film)|Black Widow]]'', which is set to be released on November 6, 2020.<ref name=\"Phase4Delay\">{{cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/black-widow-moves-to-november-as-other-mcu-films-shift-back-to-2021-2022/|title='Black Widow' Moves to November as Other MCU Films Shift Back to 2021, 2022 |last=Welk |first=Brian |website=[[TheWrap]] |date=April 3, 2020 |access-date=April 3, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200403185146/http://www.thewrap.com/black-widow-moves-to-november-as-other-mcu-films-shift-back-to-2021-2022/ |archive-date=April 3, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Concept, creation, and casting==\nBlack Widow was initially created as a comic book character named [[Black Widow (Natasha Romanova)|Natasha Romanova]], first appearing as a recurring, non-costumed, [[Russia]]n-[[espionage|spy]] antagonist in the feature \"[[Iron Man]]\", beginning in ''[[Tales of Suspense]]'' #52 (April 1964). Five issues later, she recruits the besotted costumed archer and later superhero [[Hawkeye (Clint Barton)|Hawkeye]] to her cause. Her government later supplies her with her first Black Widow costume and high-tech weaponry, but she eventually defects to the United States after appearing, temporarily brainwashed against the U.S., in the superhero-team series ''[[The Avengers (comic)|The Avengers]]'' #29 (July 1966). The Widow later becomes a recurring ally of the team before officially becoming its sixteenth member many years later. Her look was substantially revised in ''[[The Amazing Spider-Man]]'' #86 (July 1970), with shoulder-length red hair (instead of her former short black hair), a skintight black costume, and wristbands which fired spider threads.<ref name=\"back45\">{{cite journal|last= Carson|first= Lex|date= December 2010|title= Daredevil and the Black Widow: A Swinging Couple of Crimefighters|journal= [[Back Issue!]]|issue= 45| pages= 31\u201338|publisher= [[TwoMorrows Publishing]]}}</ref>\n\nIn 2004, [[Lionsgate Films|Lionsgate]] acquired the film rights for Black Widow,<ref name=\"LionsGateRights\" /> and in April announced that a ''Black Widow'' motion picture, featuring the Natasha Romanova version, was in the script stage by screenwriter-director [[David Hayter]], with [[Avi Arad]] producing.<ref name=\"HayterDirectWrite\" /><ref>{{cite web |url=http://movies.about.com/cs/upcomingreleases/a/pun2030204.htm |title=Lions Gate press release (March 2, 2004) |publisher=Movies.about.com |accessdate=January 10, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110607040255/http://movies.about.com/cs/upcomingreleases/a/pun2030204.htm |archivedate=June 7, 2011 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> By June 2006, Lionsgate had dropped the project, and the rights to the character reverted to Marvel.<ref>{{cite web|author=Stax |url=http://movies.ign.com/articles/711/711197p1.html |title=IGN.com (June 5, 2006): \"The Word on Black Widow\" |publisher=IGN |date=June 5, 2006 |accessdate=January 10, 2011}}</ref> Hayter and Marvel tried getting another financier to develop the project, but Hayter \"never felt comfortable that we had found a place that was willing to take the movie, and the character, seriously.\" This left Hayter \"heartbroken\", but he hoped the film would be made \"some day\".<ref name=\"LionsGateDrop\" />\n\nIn January 2009, Marvel entered early talks with [[Emily Blunt]] to play Black Widow in ''[[Iron Man 2]]'',<ref name=\"BluntWidow\">{{cite news|url=http://www.variety.com/article/VR1117998515|title=Emily Blunt rumored for 'Iron Man 2'|first=Michael|last=Fleming Jr.|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=January 14, 2009|accessdate=August 3, 2012|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130208222806/http://www.variety.com/article/VR1117998515|archivedate=February 8, 2013|url-status=live}}</ref> though she was unable to take the role due to a previous commitment to star in ''[[Gulliver's Travels (2010 film)|Gulliver's Travels]]''.<ref name=\"BluntOut\">{{cite news|url=http://blogs.orlandosentinel.com/entertainment_movies_blog/2009/02/emily-blunt-on-losing-black-widow.html|title=Emily Blunt on losing Black Widow\u2026|first=Roger|last=Moore|work=[[The Orlando Sentinel]]|date=February 25, 2009|accessdate=August 3, 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120611011158/http://blogs.orlandosentinel.com/entertainment_movies_blog/2009/02/emily-blunt-on-losing-black-widow.html|archivedate=June 11, 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref> In March 2009, [[Scarlett Johansson]] signed on to play Natasha Romanoff / Black Widow, with her deal including options for multiple films.<ref name=\"JohanssonMarch2009\">{{cite news|url=http://www.deadline.com/2009/03/another-iron-man-2-exclusive-scarlett-johannson-will-replace-emily-blunt-in-iron-man-2/|title=Another 'Iron Man 2' Deal: Scarlett Johannson To Replace Emily Blunt As Black Widow For Lousy Lowball Money|first=Nikki|last=Finke|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=March 11, 2009|accessdate=August 3, 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120829201759/http://www.deadline.com/2009/03/another-iron-man-2-exclusive-scarlett-johannson-will-replace-emily-blunt-in-iron-man-2/|archivedate=August 29, 2012|url-status=live}}</ref> Johansson then reprised the role in ''[[The Avengers (2012 film)|The Avengers]]'' (2012),<ref name=\"Avengers\" /><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.deadline.com/2010/07/star-wattage-marvel-assembles-the-avengers-for-comic-con-panel |title=Marvel-ous Star Wattage: Actors Assemble For Comic-Con Panel Including 'The Avengers', 'Captain America', & 'Thor{{'-}} |date=July 24, 2010 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |accessdate=July 25, 2010 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5zx6k1EnB?url=http://www.deadline.com/2010/07/star-wattage-marvel-assembles-the-avengers-for-comic-con-panel |archivedate=July 5, 2011 |url-status=live |df=mdy }}</ref> ''[[Captain America: The Winter Soldier]]'' (2014),<ref name=\"WinterSoldier\">{{cite web |first=Mike |last=Fleming |url=http://www.deadline.com/2012/10/five-actresses-testing-for-captain-america-2-role-black-widow-might-drop-by-as-well// |title=Five Actresses Testing For 'Captain America 2' Role; Black Widow Might Drop By As Well |date=October 2, 2012 |website=Deadline Hollywood |accessdate=October 2, 2012 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6B7naLneH?url=http://www.deadline.com/2012/10/five-actresses-testing-for-captain-america-2-role-black-widow-might-drop-by-as-well/ |archivedate=October 2, 2012 |url-status=live |df=mdy }}</ref> ''[[Avengers: Age of Ultron]]'' (2015),<ref name=\"AvengersAoU\" /> ''[[Captain America: Civil War]]'' (2016),<ref name=\"CapCW\" /><ref>{{cite news |date=July 25, 2013 |first=Brett |last=White |title='Avengers: Age Of Ultron' To Feature Lots More Black Widow And Hawkeye |url=http://splashpage.mtv.com/2013/07/25/avengers-age-of-ultron-black-widow-hawkeye/ |publisher=[[MTV]] |accessdate=July 25, 2013 }}</ref><ref name=\"Johansson\">{{cite web |url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/gossip/scarlett-johansson-flaunts-curves-new-magazine-photo-shoot-article-1.1470378 |title=Scarlett Johansson flaunts curves in new magazine photo shoot, reveals details on 'The Avengers' sequel |last=Maresca |first=Rachel |publisher=Daily News |date=September 29, 2013 |accessdate=September 29, 2013 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6K03pw89R?url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/gossip/scarlett-johansson-flaunts-curves-new-magazine-photo-shoot-article-1.1470378 |archivedate=September 29, 2013 |url-status=live |df=mdy }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2014/11/daniel-bruhl-captain-america-robert-downey-jr-chris-evans-1201284648/|title=Daniel Bruhl To Play Villain In 'Captain America: Civill War'|last=Fleming, Jr|first=Mike|publisher=Deadline|date=November 14, 2014}}</ref> ''[[Avengers: Infinity War]]'' (2018)<ref name=\"InfinityWar\" /><ref>Heller, Corinne (November 29, 2017). [http://www.eonline.com/news/897044/ranking-the-avengers-infinity-war-makeovers \"Ranking the ''Avengers: Infinity War'', Makeovers, From Captain America's Beard to Blonde Black Widow\"]. [[E! News]].</ref> ''[[Captain Marvel (film)|Captain Marvel]]'' (in a brief mid-credits appearance),<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theverge.com/2019/3/7/18255336/captain-marvel-post-credits-scene-avengers-endgame-flerken-alien-cat-goose-tesseract |title=One of Captain Marvel's post-credits scenes is great news for Avengers: Endgame |last=Robinson |first=Tasha |work=[[The Verge]] |publisher=[[Vox Media]] |date=March 7, 2019 |accessdate=March 8, 2019 }}</ref> and in a leading role in ''[[Avengers: Endgame]]'' (2019).<ref name=\"Endgame\" /><ref name=\"JohanssonAvengers4\">{{cite web|url=http://screenrant.com/avengers-4-images-japan-black-widow/|title=Black Widow Heads to Japan in Avengers 4 Set Photos|last=Welch|first=Alex|publisher=Screen Rant|date=August 22, 2017|accessdate=August 22, 2017|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6svCIdgLA?url=http://screenrant.com/avengers-4-images-japan-black-widow/|archivedate=August 23, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> After the release of ''Age of Ultron'', Johansson revealed that the number of films on her contract had been adjusted since she first signed to match the \"demand of the character\", as Marvel had not anticipated the audience's \"great reaction\" to the character and her performance.<ref name=\"JohanssonApril2015\" />\n\nIn September 2010, while promoting the home media release of ''Iron Man 2'', Marvel Studios President [[Kevin Feige]] indicated interest in producing a solo ''Black Widow'' film,<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|first=Phil |last=Pirrello |url=http://movies.ign.com/articles/112/1122862p1.html |title=Black Widow: The Movie? |publisher=IGN |date=September 22, 2010 |accessdate=January 10, 2011}}</ref> and stated that discussions with Johansson had already taken place regarding a Black Widow standalone film, but that Marvel's focus was on 2012's ''[[The Avengers (2012 film)|The Avengers]]''.<ref name=\"IGNSep2010\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2010/09/22/black-widow-the-movie|title=Black Widow: The Movie?|last=Pirrello|first=Phil|website=[[IGN]]|date=September 22, 2010|accessdate=July 26, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141031171000/http://www.ign.com/articles/2010/09/22/black-widow-the-movie|archivedate=October 31, 2014|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2014, Feige stated that, after exploring Black Widow's past in ''Age of Ultron'', he would like to see it explored further in a solo film, which already had development work done for it,<ref name=\"BlackWidowSolo\" /><ref name=\"auto1\">{{cite web |url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2014/02/13/feige-black-widows-past-to-be-explored-in-avengers-2-and-possible-solo-film |title=Feige: Black Widow's Past to be Explored in Avengers 2 and Possible Solo Film |last=Couto |first=Anthony |publisher=IGN |date=February 12, 2014 |accessdate=February 13, 2014 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6NLi44Kpu?url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2014/02/13/feige-black-widows-past-to-be-explored-in-avengers-2-and-possible-solo-film |archivedate=February 13, 2014 |url-status=live |df=mdy }}</ref> including a \"pretty in depth\" treatment by [[Nicole Perlman]], who co-wrote Marvel's ''[[Guardians of the Galaxy (film)|Guardians of the Galaxy]]'' (2014).<ref name=\"PerlmanWidow\" /> The following April, Johansson expressed interest in starring in a Black Widow film, and said that it would be driven by demand from the audience.<ref name=\"JohanssonApr2014\" /> That July, Hayter expressed interest in reviving the project for Marvel,<ref name=\"HayterRevive\" /> and the following month, director [[Neil Marshall]] stated that he \"would {{em|love}} to do a Black Widow film,\" saying he felt the character was \"really interesting [given] she doesn't have any superpowers, she just has extraordinary skills, and the world that she comes from, being this ex-K.G.B. assassin, I find that really fascinating.\"<ref name=\"Marshall\" /> In April 2015, Johansson spoke more on the possibility of a solo Black Widow film, seeing the potential to explore the different \"layers\" of her depicted in the different films so far, but also stating that \"right now I think this character is used well in this part of the universe\".<ref name=\"JohanssonApril2015\" /> While promoting ''Captain America: Civil War'' the next April, Feige noted that due to the announced schedule of films, any potential ''Black Widow'' film would be four or five years away.<ref name=\"FeigeApril2016\" /> He added that Marvel was \"creatively and emotionally\" committed to making a ''Black Widow'' film eventually.<ref name=\"FeigeMay2016\" />\n\nIn July 2016, [[Joss Whedon]], the director of ''The Avengers'' and ''Avengers: Age of Ultron'', stated that he was open to directing a ''Black Widow'' film, feeling he could make \"a spy thriller. Like really do a good, paranoid, '[[John le Carr\u00e9]] on crack\u2019 sort of thing.\"<ref name=\"WhedonJuly2016\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2016/07/24/comic-con-2016-joss-whedon-would-direct-a-black-widow-movie-if-marvel-asked|title=Comic-Con 2016: Joss Whedon Would Direct a Black Widow Movie if Marvel Asked|last=Yehl|first=Joshua|website=[[IGN]]|date=July 23, 2016|accessdate=July 25, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160725085953/http://www.ign.com/articles/2016/07/24/comic-con-2016-joss-whedon-would-direct-a-black-widow-movie-if-marvel-asked|archivedate=July 25, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> In October, Johansson discussed the potential film being a prequel, saying, \"you can bring it back to Russia. You could explore the Widow program. There's all kinds of stuff that you could do with it.\" She did caution she may not want to \"wear a skin-tight catsuit\" for much longer.<ref name=\"JohanssonOct2016\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/scarlett-johansson-black-widow-movie-avengers-trump-1201887106/|title=Scarlett Johansson on Black Widow Movie, 'The Avengers' and Donald Trump|last=Setoodeh|first=Ramin|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=October 12, 2016|accessdate=October 14, 2016|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161013125021/http://variety.com/2016/film/news/scarlett-johansson-black-widow-movie-avengers-trump-1201887106/|archivedate=October 13, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> The next February, Johansson said that she would dedicate herself to making any potential Black Widow film \"amazing. It would have to be the best version that movie could possibly be. Otherwise, I would never do it ... [it would] have to be its own standalone and its own style and its own story.\"<ref name=\"JohanssonFeb2017\">{{cite web|url=http://www.gamesradar.com/the-black-widow-movie-should-be-done-says-scarlett-johansson/|title=The Black Widow movie \"should be done\" says Scarlett Johansson|last=Russell|first=Bradley|website=[[GamesRadar+]]|date=February 10, 2017|accessdate=February 10, 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170211024205/http://www.gamesradar.com/the-black-widow-movie-should-be-done-says-scarlett-johansson/|archivedate=February 11, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> Following the development work done and the public support for a Black Widow film to be made, Marvel ultimately decided that the \"best time to move forward with the project\" would be at the beginning of the \"latest phase\" of the MCU in 2020.<ref name=\"PughVariety\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/florence-pugh-scarlett-johansson-black-widow-1203165665/|title=Scarlett Johansson\u2019s \u2018Black Widow\u2019 Movie Adds Florence Pugh|last=Kroll|first=Justin|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=March 18, 2019|accessdate=March 20, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190319085011/https://variety.com/2019/film/news/florence-pugh-scarlett-johansson-black-widow-1203165665/|archivedate=March 19, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2018, [[Jac Schaeffer]] was hired to write the script.<ref name=\"auto2\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/marvel-black-widow-jac-schaeffer-screenwriter-1202643908/|title=Marvel's Standalone 'Black Widow' Movie Gains Momentum With Jac Schaeffer Writing|last=Kroll|first=Justin|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=January 10, 2018|accessdate=January 10, 2018|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6wNiu5dxJ?url=http://variety.com/2018/film/news/marvel-black-widow-jac-schaeffer-screenwriter-1202643908/|archivedate=January 11, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> That July, [[Cate Shortland]] was hired to direct.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/black-widow-movie-be-directed-by-cate-shortland-1126708|title='Black Widow' Movie Finds Director in Cate Shortland (Exclusive)|last=Kit|first=Borys|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=July 12, 2018|accessdate=July 12, 2018|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/70riB79jH?url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/black-widow-movie-be-directed-by-cate-shortland-1126708|archivedate=July 12, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Marvel sought a female director for the project, part of a priority push by major film studios to hire female directors for franchises.<ref name=\"Apr2018Directors\" /><ref name=\"ShortlandDirect\" /> [[Cate Shortland]] had the backing of Johansson, a fan of the director's previous female-starring film ''[[Lore (film)|Lore]]'' (2012), and was hired to direct ''Black Widow''.<ref name=\"ShortlandDirect\" /> ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' reported in October 2018 that Johansson would earn $15 million to appear in the film, an increase from the \"low-seven figure salary\" she earned for starring in ''The Avengers''. The $15 million was equal to what [[Chris Evans (actor)|Chris Evans]] and [[Chris Hemsworth]] each earned in ''Captain America: Civil War'', ''[[Thor: Ragnarok]]'', ''Avengers: Infinity War'', and ''Avengers: Endgame''. Despite ''The Hollywood Reporter'' confirming the amount from \"multiple knowledgable sources\", Marvel Studios disputed the accuracy of the numbers while stating that they \"never publicly disclose salaries or deal terms.\"<ref name=\"JohannsonPayOct2018\" /> The film was expected to be released in May 2020, but was delayed due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2020/film/box-office/black-widow-release-coronavirus-1203532996/|title=\u2018Black Widow\u2019 Release Pulled Amid Coronavirus Pandemic|first=Rebecca|last=Rubin|publisher=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=March 17, 2020}}</ref> with the new release date being November 6, 2020.<ref name=\"Phase4Delay\"/>\n\n==Characterization==\n[[File:Scarlett Johansson by Gage Skidmore 2 (cropped).jpg|thumb|Scarlett Johansson speaking on the ''[[Black Widow (2020 film)|Black Widow]]'' panel at the 2019 San Diego Comic-Con International in San Diego, California.]]\nIn ''Iron Man 2'', Romanoff is introduced as Natalie Rushman, an undercover spy for S.H.I.E.L.D. posing as Stark's new assistant. Johansson dyed her hair red before she landed the part, hoping that it would help convince Favreau that she was right for the role.<ref name=\"JohanssonRedHair\">{{Cite web|first=Rebecca |last=Murray |title=Scarlett Johansson Interview &ndash; 'Iron Man 2' |url=http://movies.about.com/od/ironman2/a/scarlett-johansson.htm |work=About.com |accessdate=August 3, 2012 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6A5VQqK4u?url=http://movies.about.com/od/ironman2/a/scarlett-johansson.htm |archivedate=August 21, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> Johansson said that she chose the role because \"the Black Widow character resonated with me... [She] is a superhero, but she's also human. She's small, but she's strong... She is dark and has faced death so many times that she has a deep perspective on the value of life... It's hard not to admire her.\"<ref name=\"JohanssonFeb2015\">{{cite web|url=http://www.wmagazine.com/people/celebrities/2015/02/scarlett-johansson-new-mom-the-avengers/ |title=Scarlett Johansson Is Nobody's Baby |last=Hirschberg |first=Lynn |work=[[W (magazine)|W]] |date=February 9, 2015 |accessdate=February 17, 2015 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6WQ0WepJM?url=http://www.wmagazine.com/people/celebrities/2015/02/scarlett-johansson-new-mom-the-avengers/ |archivedate=February 17, 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref> She stated that she had \"a bit of a freak-out moment\" when she first saw the cat-suit.<ref name=\"JohanssonComicCon\">{{Cite news|date=July 28, 2009 |first=Steve |last=Weintraub |title=Scarlett Johansson Comic-Con Interview IRON MAN 2 |url=http://collider.com/scarlett-johansson-comic-con-interview-iron-man-2/4810/ |work=Collider.com |accessdate=August 3, 2012 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6A5V5We4S?url=http://collider.com/scarlett-johansson-comic-con-interview-iron-man-2/4810/ |archivedate=August 21, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> When asked about fighting in the costume, Johansson responded \"a big part of me is like 'can I move in this? Can I run in it? Can I like throw myself over things with this?' And I think just the prep, you just have to put in the hours. That's what I realized is that just putting in the hours and doing the training and repetition and basically just befriending the stunt team and spending all day, every day, just over and over and over and over until you sell it.\"<ref name=\"JohanssonComicCon\" />\n\nIn ''The Avengers'', the character's close friendship with Clint Barton is indicated, about which Johansson said, \"Our characters have a long history. They've fought together for a long time in a lot of battles in many different countries. We're the two members of this avenging group who are skilled warriors \u2013 we have no superpowers. Black Widow is definitely one of the team, though. She's not in the cast simply to be a romantic foil or eye candy. She's there to fight, so I never felt like I was the only girl. We all have our various skills and it feels equal\".<ref name=\"Filmink\">{{cite journal|last=Adamek|first=Pauline|date=January\u2013February 2012|title=Avengers Assemble!|journal=[[Filmink]]|pages=70\u201375|publisher=FKP International Exports}}</ref> Regarding her training, Johansson said, \"Even though ''Iron Man 2'' was 'one-for-them,' I'd never done anything like that before. I'd never been physically driven in something, or a part of something so big. For ''The Avengers'', I've spent so many months training with our stunt team, and fighting all the other actors, it's crazy. I do nothing but fight\u2014all the time.\"<ref name=\"Biskind\">{{cite web |last=Biskind |first=Peter |date=December 2011 |title=A Study in Scarlett |url=http://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/features/2011/12/scarlett-johansson-201112 |work=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]] |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/63MX9meNm?url=http://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/features/2011/12/scarlett-johansson-201112 |archivedate=November 21, 2011 |url-status=live |accessdate=November 21, 2011}}</ref> Johansson earned $4-6 million for the film.<ref name=\"CastPay\">{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/marvel-moolah-robert-downey-jr-avengers-iron-man-324639|title=Marvel Moolah: Robert Downey Jr. 'Avengers' Pay Set to Hit $50 Million|last=Belloni|first=Matthew|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=May 15, 2012|accessdate=October 11, 2018|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/735rCU3kB?url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/marvel-moolah-robert-downey-jr-avengers-iron-man-324639|archivedate=October 11, 2018|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nIn ''Captain America: The Winter Soldier'', Screenwriter Christopher Markus said that Black Widow was a \"great contrast\" to Captain America, describing her as \"incredibly modern, not very reverent, and just very straightforward whereas Steve is, you know a man from the 40s. He's not a boy scout, but he is reserved and has a moral center, whereas her moral center moves.\"<ref name=\"MarkusMcFeelyApril2013Collider\">{{cite web|date=April 12, 2013 |last=Chitwood |first=Adam |title=Christopher Markus and Stephen McFeely Talk Captain America 2 and Thor 2; Reveal Cap 2 Has Faster Pace & Fewer Flashbacks Than Initially Planned |url=http://collider.com/captain-america-2-news-story-details-christopher-markus-stephen-mcfeely/ |publisher=Collider.com |accessdate=April 12, 2013 |archivedate=April 14, 2013 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130414230556/http://collider.com/captain-america-2-news-story-details-christopher-markus-stephen-mcfeely/ |url-status=live}}</ref> The Russos added, \"She's a character who lies for a living. That's what she does. He's a character who tells the truth. Give them a problem and they'll have different ways of approaching it. She's pushing him to modernize, and he's pushing her to add a certain level of integrity to her life.\"<ref name=\"IGNMar2014pg3\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2014/03/06/the-winter-soldier-has-america-changed-too-much-for-captain-america?page=3 |title=The Winter Soldier: Has America Changed Too Much for Captain America? |last=Goldman |first=Eric |website=IGN |date=March 6, 2014 |accessdate=March 10, 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140311121949/http://www.ign.com/articles/2014/03/06/the-winter-soldier-has-america-changed-too-much-for-captain-america?page=3 |archivedate=March 11, 2014 |url-status=live}}</ref> When asked about Romanoff's relationship with Rogers, Johansson responded, \"By a series of unfortunate encounters, they will be in a situation in which their friendship becomes more intimate. They share many similarities because they live on the defensive without relying on anyone. Also, the two have been working for the government throughout their professional careers. With their friendship they begin to question what they want and what is their true identity.\"<ref name=\"Refinery29\">{{cite web |last=Lussier |first=Germain |title=Scarlett Johansson Dishes on 'Top Chef' and Porn |publisher=Refinery29.com | url = http://www.refinery29.com/2013/09/54387/scarlett-johansson-don-jon-interview |date=September 29, 2013| first2= Jordan | last2= Riefe | accessdate = February 12, 2013 | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131006094151/http://www.refinery29.com/2013/09/54387/scarlett-johansson-don-jon-interview |archivedate = October 6, 2013 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nProducer [[Kevin Feige]] stated that more of the character's backstory is explored in ''Avengers: Age of Ultron''.<ref name=\"BlackWidowBackstory\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2014/02/13/feige-black-widows-past-to-be-explored-in-avengers-2-and-possible-solo-film |title=Feige: Black Widow's Past to be Explored in Avengers 2 and Possible Solo Film |last=Couto |first=Anthony |publisher=[[IGN]] |date=February 12, 2014 |accessdate=February 13, 2014 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6NLi44Kpu?url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2014/02/13/feige-black-widows-past-to-be-explored-in-avengers-2-and-possible-solo-film |archivedate=February 13, 2014 |url-status=live |df=mdy }}</ref> Johansson elaborated, \"In ''Avengers 2'' we go back... we definitely learn more about Widow's backstory, and we get to find out how she became the person you see. All of these characters have deep, dark pasts, and I think that the past catches up to some of us a little bit.\"<ref name=\"Johansson2\">{{cite AV media |people=Johannson, Scarlett |date=March 19, 2014 |title=Scarlett Johansson Talks The Avengers: Age of Ultron |medium=video |url=http://www.ign.com/videos/2014/03/20/scarlett-johansson-talks-the-avengers-age-of-ultron |accessdate=March 20, 2014 |publisher=[[IGN]]}}</ref> Regarding where the film picks up Widow's story, Johansson felt it was a continuation of what was seen for her character in ''The Winter Soldier'', with the fact that \"'[Widow] never made an active choice. [She's] a product of other people's imposition.' That's going to catch up with her. That's bound to have a huge effect. There's got to be a result of that realization... You'll see her actively making some choices in her life, for better or worse.\"<ref name=\"Johansson3\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2014/07/17/avengers-age-of-ultron-scarlett-johansson-talks-black-widows-greatest-power |title=Avengers: Age Of Ultron Scarlett Johansson Talks Black Widow's Greatest Power |last=Cornet |first=Roth |publisher=[[IGN]] |date=July 17, 2014 |accessdate=July 17, 2014 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6R99TUrzn?url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2014/07/17/avengers-age-of-ultron-scarlett-johansson-talks-black-widows-greatest-power |archivedate=July 18, 2014 |url-status=live |df=mdy }}</ref> A mixture of close-ups, concealing costumes, stunt doubles and visual effects were used to help hide Johansson's pregnancy during filming.<ref name=\"JohanssonPregnancyEW\">{{cite web|url=http://insidemovies.ew.com/2014/07/18/avengers-age-of-ultron-scarlett-johanssons-pregnancy/ |title=How 'Avengers: Age of Ultron' will hide Scarlett Johansson's pregnancy |last=Breznican |first=Anthony |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |date=July 18, 2014 |accessdate=July 18, 2014 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6RAdLPGJO?url=http://insidemovies.ew.com/2014/07/18/avengers-age-of-ultron-scarlett-johanssons-pregnancy/ |archivedate=July 19, 2014 |url-status=live |df=mdy }}</ref>\n\nAnthony Russo noted Romanoff's torn allegiances in ''Captain America: Civil War'', saying \"her head is with Tony's side of things, but her heart is with Cap in a lot of ways.\"<ref name=\"RussosEmpire\">{{cite web|url=http://www.empireonline.com/movies/features/captain-america-civil-war-trailer-breakdown/ |title=Captain America: Civil War trailer breakdown |last=Hewitt |first=Chris |work=[[Empire (film magazine)|Empire]] |date=November 25, 2015 |accessdate=November 25, 2015 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6dJT8QBJ6?url=http://www.empireonline.com/movies/features/captain-america-civil-war-trailer-breakdown/ |archivedate=November 25, 2015 |url-status=live  }}</ref> Johansson added that Romanoff is \"looking to strategize her position, putting herself in a place where she is able to let the powers that be fight it out\" in order for her to \"have a better perspective of what's really going on\".<ref name=\"JohanssonEWpg2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2015/12/03/captain-america-civil-war-black-widow/2 |title=Captain America: Civil War star Scarlett Johansson on the scrutiny of Black Widow |last=Breznican |first=Anthony |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |date=December 3, 2015 |accessdate=December 3, 2015 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6dW5IgHIs?url=http://www.ew.com/article/2015/12/03/captain-america-civil-war-black-widow/2 |archivedate=December 4, 2015 |url-status=live  }}</ref> Describing her character's situation after the events of ''Avengers: Age of Ultron'', Johansson said, \"I think that the Widow's past will always haunt her. She's trying to move forward, she's trying to pick up the pieces of her life\".<ref name=\"Johansson Teases\">{{cite web|date=April 21, 2015 |url=http://www.ign.com/videos/2015/04/21/scarlett-johansson-teases-her-role-in-captain-america-civil-war |title=Captain America: Civil War \u2013 Scarlett Johansson Teases Her Role In Captain America: Civil War |website=[[IGN]] |accessdate=April 22, 2015 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6XzVbnkgB?url=http://www.ign.com/videos/2015/04/21/scarlett-johansson-teases-her-role-in-captain-america-civil-war |archivedate=April 23, 2015 |url-status=live  }}</ref> She also said that Romanoff is at a point in her life where she can make choices herself, without having others have a hand in the decision process.<ref name=\"JohanssonEW 2015\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2015/12/03/captain-america-civil-war-black-widow |title=Captain America: Civil War star Scarlett Johansson on the scrutiny of Black Widow |last=Breznican |first=Anthony |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |date=December 3, 2015 |accessdate=December 3, 2015 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6dVwE8CXM?url=http://www.ew.com/article/2015/12/03/captain-america-civil-war-black-widow |archivedate=December 4, 2015 |url-status=live  }}</ref> On the continuation of the relationship between Romanoff and Rogers from ''The Winter Soldier'', Joe Russo said that they wanted to \"test it\" by having Romanoff point out to Rogers the mistakes the team have made and convince him \"that it might not be as black and white as he sees it\" and that the Avengers must \"find a way to work within the system so that [they] aren't disbanded\".<ref name=\"RussosEmpire\" />\n\nBy the events of ''Infinity War'', Johansson said that Romanoff's situation following ''Captain America: Civil War'' has been \"a dark time. I wouldn't say that my character has been particularly hopeful, but I think she's hardened even more than she probably was before\".<ref name=\"EWBTSPg3\">{{cite web|url=http://ew.com/movies/2018/03/08/avengers-infinity-war-behind-the-scenes/3/|title=Behind the scenes of Avengers: Infinity War as new heroes unite \u2013 and others will end \u2013 page 3|last=Breznican|first=Anthony|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=March 8, 2018|accessdate=March 8, 2018|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6xlqwcUGe?url=http://ew.com/movies/2018/03/08/avengers-infinity-war-behind-the-scenes/3/|archivedate=March 8, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> At the beginning of ''Avengers: Endgame'', Romanoff continues to command several teams from around the galaxy in the Avengers headquarters, which Joe Russo explained was stemmed from her inability to move on from their failure to stop Thanos, saying, \"she's doing everything she can to try and hold the community together...She's the watcher on the wall still.\"<ref name=\"ControWidow\">{{Cite web |url=https://ew.com/movies/2019/05/02/avengers-endgame-directors-black-widow-scene/ |title=Avengers: Endgame directors defend controversial Black Widow scene |last=Breznican |first=Anthony |date=May 2, 2019 |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |access-date=May 15, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190507013118/https://ew.com/movies/2019/05/02/avengers-endgame-directors-black-widow-scene/ |archive-date=May 7, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> On the decision for Romanoff to sacrifice herself for Barton to acquire the Soul Stone to bring back everyone, Joe Russo stated that it was part of a larger theme exploring the desire to sacrifice, compared to the desire to protect in ''Infinity War''; he says, \"When she gets to that [Soul Stone] scene, I think she understands that the only way to bring the community back is for her to sacrifice herself.\"<ref name=\"ControWidow\" /> McFeely stated, \"Her journey, in our minds, had come to an end if she could get the Avengers back. She comes from such an abusive, terrible, mind-control background, so when she gets to Vormir and she has a chance to get the family back, that's a thing she would trade for.\"<ref name=\"NYMarkusMcFeely\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/29/movies/avengers-endgame-questions-and-answers.html |title='Avengers: Endgame': The Screenwriters Answer Every Question You Might Have |last=Itzkoff |first=Dave |date=April 29, 2019 |work=[[The New York Times]] |access-date=May 15, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190514173025/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/29/movies/avengers-endgame-questions-and-answers.html |archive-date=May 14, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> To prepare for the film, Johansson underwent a high-intensity workout regimen, which included [[plyometrics]], [[Olympic weightlifting]] and gymnastics, as well as a time-restricted eating diet; all are under the supervision of her longtime trainer, Eric Johnson, with whom she had worked since ''[[Iron Man 2]]'' (2010), the film which introduced her character.<ref name=\"JohanssonPrepare\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/scarlett-johanssons-avengers-workout-how-get-a-black-widow-body-1204043 |title=Scarlett Johansson's 'Avengers' Workout: How to Get a Black Widow Body |last=Romeyn |first=Kathryn |date=April 26, 2019 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |access-date=May 15, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190502183033/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/scarlett-johanssons-avengers-workout-how-get-a-black-widow-body-1204043 |archive-date=May 2, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nJohansson described the film, ''[[Black Widow (2020 film)|Black Widow]]'' as \"an opportunity to explore the Widow as a woman who has come into her own and is making independent and active choices for herself, probably for once in her life\".<ref name=\"DeadlineNov2018\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/11/spider-women-captain-marvel-and-harley-quinn-females-fly-in-the-face-of-old-hollywood-perceptions-1202485612/|title=Spider-Women, Captain Marvel & Harley Quinn: Females Fly In The Face Of Old Hollywood Perceptions|last1=Boucher|first1=Geoff|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=November 30, 2018|accessdate=November 30, 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181201000807/https://deadline.com/2018/11/spider-women-captain-marvel-and-harley-quinn-females-fly-in-the-face-of-old-hollywood-perceptions-1202485612/|archivedate=December 1, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Character biography==\n===Early life===\nBorn in Russia in 1984, Natasha Romanoff was trained as a spy in a secretive academy called the [[Red Room (comics)|Red Room]] which involved training as a [[ballerina]] as a cover,<ref name=\"Disgrace\">{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2015/05/05/avengers-age-of-ultron-s-black-widow-disgrace|title=\u2018Avengers: Age of Ultron\u2019s\u2019 Black Widow Disgrace|first=Marlow|last=Stern|date=5 May 2015|publisher=|via=www.thedailybeast.com}}</ref> as well as the eventual [[Sterilization (medicine)|sterilization]] of the students.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://uproxx.com/hitfix/lets-talk-about-black-widows-sterilization-scene-in-avengers-age-of-ultron/|title=Why Black Widow\u2019s sterilization scene in \u2018Age of Ultron\u2019 is astonishing|date=7 May 2015|publisher=}}</ref> Eventually, [[Clint Barton (Marvel Cinematic Universe)|Clint Barton]] is sent to kill Romanoff, but instead chooses to spare her life and recruit her to [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]], enabling Romanoff to escape her previous life as an assassin.\n\n===Undercover for S.H.I.E.L.D.===\nAfter [[Tony Stark (Marvel Cinematic Universe)|Tony Stark]] publicly becomes Iron Man and appoints his personal assistant [[Pepper Potts]] as CEO of Stark Industries, he hires Stark employee Natalie Rushman to replace Potts as his personal assistant, unaware that Rushman is actually Natasha Romanoff undercover. [[Nick Fury]], director of S.H.I.E.L.D., later reveals this to Stark, and Romanoff then helps Stark to thwart the plans of villains [[Justin Hammer]] and [[Ivan Vanko]], the latter of whom has remotely taken control of an army of military drones and the armor of Stark's friend James Rhodes. Romanoff successfully defeats Hammer's security forces to return control of the Rhodes' armor, allowing Stark and Rhodes to defeat Vanko and the drones.\n===Battle of New York===\nSome months later, while Loki begins his attack on Earth, Romanoff is being held prisoner and interrogated by Russians. Agent [[Phil Coulson]] is able to contact Romanoff to inform her that Loki has compromised Barton, and Romanoff promptly overcomes her captors, whom she had only allowed to capture her as a ploy to extract information. Romanoff recruits [[Bruce Banner (Marvel Cinematic Universe)|Bruce Banner]] from his seclusion in [[Kolkata]] to use his expertise to track the gamma signature of Loki's scepter. On board S.H.I.E.L.D.'s helicarrier, she tricks Loki into revealing his plan to cause Banner to become the Hulk, but is too late, as Barton and Loki's other possessed agents attack the Helicarrier, causing Banner to transform into the Hulk and pursue Romanoff until he is distracted by [[Thor (Marvel Cinematic Universe)|Thor]]. Romanoff reluctantly fights Barton, and knocks him unconscious, breaking Loki's mind control. [[Steve Rogers (Marvel Cinematic Universe)|Rogers]], Stark, Romanoff, Barton, Thor, and Hulk then rally in defense of Loki's next target, New York City.\n===Working with Captain America===\nTwo years after the [[The Avengers (2012 film)|Battle of New York]], Romanoff and Rogers are sent with S.H.I.E.L.D.'s [[counter-terrorism]] [[S.T.R.I.K.E.]] team to free hostages aboard a S.H.I.E.L.D. vessel from [[Batroc the Leaper|Georges Batroc]] and his mercenaries. Mid-mission, Rogers discovers Romanoff has another agenda: to extract data from the ship's computers for Fury. After an attempt on Fury's life, Rogers becomes a fugitive hunted by S.T.R.I.K.E., and meets with Romanoff. Using data in the flash drive, they discover a secret S.H.I.E.L.D. bunker in New Jersey, where they activate a supercomputer containing the [[mind uploading|preserved consciousness]] of [[Arnim Zola]]. Zola reveals that ever since S.H.I.E.L.D. was founded after [[World War II]], [[Hydra (comics)|Hydra]] has secretly operated within its ranks, sowing global chaos with the objective of making humanity surrender its freedom in exchange for security. The pair narrowly escape death when a S.H.I.E.L.D. missile destroys the bunker, and realize that Secretary of Internal Security [[Alexander Pierce]] is Hydra's leader within S.H.I.E.L.D. To prevent Hydra from using helicarriers to attack the world's superheroes, Romanoff, disguised as a World Security Council member, disarms Pierce. Fury arrives and forces Pierce to unlock S.H.I.E.L.D.'s database so that Romanoff can leak classified information, exposing Hydra to the public. Romanoff later appears before a Senate subcommittee, while Fury, under the cover of his apparent death, heads to Eastern Europe in pursuit of Hydra's remaining cells.\n===Battle of Sokovia and Civil War===\nRomanoff continues to work with the Avengers, helping them to attack a Hydra facility where they recover Loki's scepter. She becomes romantically involved with Banner, but he and Stark accidentally create Ultron, who captures Romanoff and takes her to Sokovia. Rescued by Banner, she pushes him off a ledge to force his transformation into the Hulk to aid in the battle against Ultron, an act which later influences Hulk to leave Earth altogether. Sokovia is destroyed in the battle, leading to the passage of the Sokovia Accords, over which Tony Stark and Steve Rogers have a falling out. Romanoff initially sides with Stark's team, accompanying them to battle Rogers and his allies at Leipzig Airport, but Romanoff then switches sides to allow Rogers to escape with Bucky Barnes.\n===The Infinity War===\nRomanoff later reconnects with a fugitive Rogers, and, two years after the passing of the Sokovia Accords, when Thanos sends his minions to retrieve Infinity Stones on Earth, she, Rogers, and [[Sam Wilson (Marvel Cinematic Universe)|Sam Wilson]] arrive in Scotland in time to defend [[Wanda Maximoff (Marvel Cinematic Universe)|Wanda Maximoff]] and [[Vision (Marvel Cinematic Universe)|Vision]] from an attack by members of the Black Order. She travels to [[Wakanda]] to aid in the battle against the forces of Thanos, but the defenders are unable to prevent Thanos from obtaining the stones and using them to eliminate half of all life in the Universe. \n\nRomanoff survives the snap, and travels with the newly arrived Captain Marvel and other surviving Avengers to Thanos' garden planet to attempt to recover the Infinity Stones, only to learn that Thanos has already destroyed them. Romanoff then returns to Earth to continue to lead the remnants of S.H.I.E.L.D. and the Avengers from the former Avengers headquarters in upstate New York.\n\nFive years after the Infinity War, [[Scott Lang (Marvel Cinematic Universe)|Scott Lang]] comes to the Avengers headquarters and informs Romanoff and Rogers that he has been trapped in the quantum realm, where time passes differently, affording a means to steal the Infinity Stones from the past and bring back those who were destroyed by Thanos. After working to recruit Stark and Banner to the cause, Romanoff travels to a past version of the planet Vormir with Barton. After an initial scuffle with him over the decision regarding whom to sacrifice for the Soul Stone, Romanoff sacrifices her life so that Barton can obtain the Soul Stone and eventually return to his family. The original five members following the mission later mourn her death and honor her sacrifice, with Banner finally using the Stark Gauntlet to bring the disintegrated back to life. Banner later notes that he had tried at that time to also bring Romanoff back, and had been unable.\n\n==Differences from the comics==\nRomanoff in the MCU is a founding member of the Avengers, while in the comics she is a much later addition, and initially an antagonist to the team. This version also showed a romance with [[Bruce Banner (Marvel Cinematic Universe)|Bruce Banner]] that was mostly explored in ''Age of Ultron'' but hinted at in later and previous films. She is also very close to Clint Barton's family, unlike in the Ultimate Comics where she murders each member before she is killed by Hawkeye.\n\n==Reception==\nDavid Edelstein of ''[[New York Magazine]]'' described the presence of the female leads in ''Iron Man 2'' as \"a gam-off between Gwyneth Paltrow and Scarlett Johansson in which Paltrow wins on length and then disappears in the glare of her opponent's headlights\".<ref name=\"NewYorkMagReview\">{{Cite web|date=May 2, 2010 |url=http://nymag.com/movies/reviews/65745/ |author=David Edelstein |title=Battle of the Rehabbed Stars |work=[[New York Magazine]] |accessdate=May 4, 2010 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6AJTLsz4h?url=http://nymag.com/movies/reviews/65745/ |archivedate=August 30, 2012 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]'' notes that her entrance in that film \"famously chose to focus on her desirability rather than her staggering combat skills\".<ref name=\"VFHowEndgame\">{{cite web|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2019/04/avengers-endgame-black-widow-death-scarlett-johansson|title=How Avengers: Endgame Failed Black Widow|first=Laura|last=Bradley|publisher=[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]|date=April 26, 2019}}</ref>\n\nA ''Daily Beast'' review of the character's role in ''Age of Ultron'' lamented that the character had been made to \"function as a cog that services the storylines\" of the male characters.<ref name=\"Disgrace\"/> ''Vanity Fair'' described the development of the character across the films as \"a trajectory that's been as all over the map as Black Widow's varying hairstyles\", stating that she \"spent her years in the MCU as an accessory to narratives foregrounding other heroes\".<ref name=\"VFHowEndgame\"/>\n\nVox notes that in ''Avengers: Endgame'', \"Johansson takes Romanoff \u2014 usually the dependable, no-frills assassin \u2014 into quiet, stoic suffering\",<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vox.com/culture/2019/4/23/18512851/avengers-endgame-review-marvel-miracle|title=Avengers: Endgame is a Marvel miracle|first=Alex|last=Abad-Santosalex|publisher=Vox|date=April 23, 2019}}</ref> while ''Vanity Fair'' laments that the film \"never gives her or her death room to breathe\".<ref name=\"VFHowEndgame\"/>\n\n===Accolades===\n{{Anchor|Awards|Accolades}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Film\n! Award\n! Category\n! Result\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"| {{Abbr|Ref(s)|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2010\n| rowspan=\"3\"| ''[[Iron Man 2]]''\n| [[2010 Teen Choice Awards|Teen Choice Awards]]\n| [[Teen Choice Award for Choice Movie Actress \u2013 Sci-Fi/Fantasy|Choice Movie Actress: Sci-Fi/Fantasy]]\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align: center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2553497/teen-choice-awards-2010-nominees/|title=Teen Choice Awards 2010: First Round of Nominees Announced|last=Soll|first=Lindsay|website=[[MTV]]|date=June 14, 2010|accessdate=October 27, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160108020424/http://www.mtv.com/news/2553497/teen-choice-awards-2010-nominees/|archivedate=January 8, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[2010 Scream Awards|Scream Awards]]\n| Best Science Fiction Actress\n| {{won}}\n| style=\"text-align: center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://techland.time.com/2010/10/21/and-your-2010-scream-awards-winners-are/|title=And Your 2010 Scream Awards Winners Are\u2026.|last=Castillo|first=Michelle|work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|date=October 21, 2010|accessdate=October 27, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110129051207/http://techland.time.com/2010/10/21/and-your-2010-scream-awards-winners-are/|archivedate=January 29, 2011|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2011\n| [[37th Saturn Awards|Saturn Awards]]\n| [[Saturn Award for Best Supporting Actress|Best Supporting Actress]]\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://collider.com/saturn-awards-2011-nominations/|title=Inception, Let Me In, Tron, and The Walkind Dead Top the 2011 Saturn Award Nominations|last=Bettinger|first=Brendan|website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|date=February 23, 2011|accessdate=October 27, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131011205401/http://collider.com/saturn-awards-2011-nominations/|archivedate=October 11, 2013|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2012\n| rowspan=\"8\"| ''[[The Avengers (2012 film)|The Avengers]]''\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[2012 Teen Choice Awards|Teen Choice Awards]]\n| [[Teen Choice Award for Choice Movie Actress \u2013 Sci-Fi/Fantasy|Choice Movie Actress: Sci-Fi/Fantasy]]\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.celebuzz.com/2012-07-22/teen-choice-awards-2012-nominees-and-winners/|title=Teen Choice Awards 2012: Nominees and Winners (Complete List)|last=Chung|first=Gabrielle|website=[[Celebuzz]]|date=July 22, 2012|accessdate=October 27, 2019