{"title_page": "Brittany Brewer", "text_new": "{{short description|American basketball player}}\n{{Infobox basketball biography\n| name = Brittany Brewer\n| image = \n| caption = \n| width = \n| number = 20\n| team = Texas Tech Red Raiders\n| league = [[Big 12 Conference]]\n| position = [[Center]]\n| height_ft = 6\n| height_in = 5\n| weight_lb = \n| nationality = American \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1997|11|6}}\n| birth_place = [[Abilene, Texas]]\n| high_school = [[Wylie High School]]<br>(Wylie, Texas)\n| college = [[Texas Tech Lady Raiders basketball|Texas Tech]] (2016\u20132020)\n| highlights = \n* Academic All-American of the Year ([[2020 NCAA Women's Basketball All-Americans |2020]])\n}}\n'''Brittany Brewer''' (born November 6, 1997) is an American [[college basketball]] player for the [[Texas Tech Lady Raiders basketball|Texas Tech Lady Raiders]] of the [[Big 12 Conference]]. Brewer is the 2020 [[College Sports Information Directors of America|CoSIDA]] Academic All-American of the Year<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://academicallamerica.com/news/2020/3/9/2019-20-academic-all-america-ncaa-division-i-womens-basketball-teams-announced.aspx|title=2019-20 Academic All-America\u00ae NCAA Division I Women's Basketball Teams Announced|website=academicallamerica.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref> and selected to [[2020 NCAA Women's Basketball All-Americans|All-America]] Honorable Mention by the [[Associated Press]] (AP)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ncaa.com/news/basketball-women/article/2020-03-19/2020-womens-basketball-associated-press-all-america-team|title=2020 women's basketball Associated Press All-America Team announced {{!}} NCAA.com|website=www.ncaa.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>. She was also selected to First-team Academic All-American in 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://academicallamerica.com/news/2019/3/11/2018-19-google-cloud-academic-all-america-ncaa-division-i-womens-basketball-team-announced.aspx|title=2018-19 Google Cloud Academic All-America\u00ae NCAA Division I Women's Basketball Team Announced|website=academicallamerica.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref>\n\n==College career==\nBrewer started 17 games in each of her freshman and sophomore season with the Lady Raiders. In the 2018\u201319 season, she started all 31 games as a junior and added 3-point shootings to her repertoire; averaging 34.3% on 99 attempts while attempting none in her prior two years. In the 2019\u201320, Brewer once again started all 29 games as a senior and averaged a double-double of 16.6 ppg and 10.3 rpg.\n\n==Career statisitcs==\n{{WNBA player statistics legend}}\n\n===College===\n\n{{WNBA player statistics start}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left; | [[2016\u201317 NCAA Division I women's basketball season|2016\u201317]]\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[2016\u201317 Texas Tech Lady Raiders basketball team|Texas Tech]]\n| 31 || 17 || 22.3 || .452 || .000 || .604 || 5.7 || 0.5 || 0.2 || 1.7 || 1.5 || 5.8\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[2017\u201318 NCAA Division I women's basketball season|2017\u201318]]\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[2017\u201318 Texas Tech Lady Raiders basketball team|Texas Tech]]\n| 30 || 17 || 20.2 || .490 || .000 || .531 || 5.0 || 0.8 || 0.4 || 1.3 || 2.4 || 9.5\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[2018\u201319 NCAA Division I women's basketball season|2018\u201319]]\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[2018\u201319 Texas Tech Lady Raiders basketball team|Texas Tech]]\n| 31 || 31 || 31.0 || .528 || .343 || .692 || 9.1 || 1.2 || 0.7 || 2.3 || 2.5 || 16.6\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[2019\u201320 NCAA Division I women's basketball season|2019\u201320]]*\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[2019\u201320 Texas Tech Lady Raiders basketball team|Texas Tech]]\n| 29 || 29 || 31.5 || .509 || .243 || .675 || 10.3 || 0.9 || 0.7 || 4.4 || 2.5 || 16.6\n|- class=\"sortbottom\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" colspan=\"2\"| Career\n| 121 || 94 || 26.2 || .495 || .146 || .625 || 7.5 || 0.7 || 0.5 || 2.4 || 2.3 || 12.1\n{{S-end}}\n<small>* 2020 NCAA tournament cancelled due to COVID-19 pandemic</small><br>\n<small>Source: texastech.com</small><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://texastech.com/sports/womens-basketball/roster/brittany-brewer/9258|title=Brittany Brewer - Women's Basketball|website=Texas Tech Red Raiders|language=en|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nBrittany Brewer is the daughter of Jacob and  Melanie Brewer. She has found siblings, Brianna, Brooklyn, Joy and Josh. She is a major in Community, Family  and Addiction Sciences. \n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Brewer, Brittany}}\n{{Women's Basketball Academic All-America of the Year}}\n\n[[Category:1997 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:All-American college women's basketball players]]\n[[Category:American women's basketball players]]\n[[Category:Basketball players from Texas]]\n[[Category:Centers (basketball)]]\n[[Category:Texas Tech Lady Raiders basketball players]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American basketball player}}\n{{Infobox basketball biography\n| name = Brittany Brewer\n| image = \n| caption = \n| width = \n| number = 20\n| team = Texas Tech Red Raiders\n| league = [[Big 12 Conference]]\n| position = [[Center]]\n| height_ft = 6\n| height_in = 5\n| weight_lb = \n| nationality = American \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1997|11|6}}\n| birth_place = [[Abilene, Texas]]\n| high_school = [[Wylie High School]]<br>(Wylie, Texas)\n| college = [[Texas Tech Lady Raiders basketball|Texas Tech]] (2016\u20132020)\n| highlights = \n* Academic All-America of the Year ([[2020 NCAA Women's Basketball All-Americans |2020]])\n}}\n'''Brittany Brewer''' (born November 6, 1997) is an American [[college basketball]] player for the [[Texas Tech Lady Raiders basketball|Texas Tech Lady Raiders]] of the [[Big 12 Conference]]. Brewer is the 2020 [[College Sports Information Directors of America|CoSIDA]] Academic All-American of the Year<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://academicallamerica.com/news/2020/3/9/2019-20-academic-all-america-ncaa-division-i-womens-basketball-teams-announced.aspx|title=2019-20 Academic All-America\u00ae NCAA Division I Women's Basketball Teams Announced|website=academicallamerica.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref> and selected to [[2020 NCAA Women's Basketball All-Americans|All-America]] Honorable Mention by the [[Associated Press]] (AP)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ncaa.com/news/basketball-women/article/2020-03-19/2020-womens-basketball-associated-press-all-america-team|title=2020 women's basketball Associated Press All-America Team announced {{!}} NCAA.com|website=www.ncaa.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>. She was also selected to First-team Academic All-American in 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://academicallamerica.com/news/2019/3/11/2018-19-google-cloud-academic-all-america-ncaa-division-i-womens-basketball-team-announced.aspx|title=2018-19 Google Cloud Academic All-America\u00ae NCAA Division I Women's Basketball Team Announced|website=academicallamerica.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref>\n\n==College career==\nBrewer started 17 games in each of her freshman and sophomore season with the Lady Raiders. In the 2018\u201319 season, she started all 31 games as a junior and added 3-point shootings to her repertoire; averaging 34.3% on 99 attempts while attempting none in her prior two years. In the 2019\u201320, Brewer once again started all 29 games as a senior and averaged a double-double of 16.6 ppg and 10.3 rpg.\n\n==Career statisitcs==\n{{WNBA player statistics legend}}\n\n===College===\n\n{{WNBA player statistics start}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left; | [[2016\u201317 NCAA Division I women's basketball season|2016\u201317]]\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| [[2016\u201317 Texas Tech Lady Raiders basketball team|Texas Tech]]\n| 31 || 17 || 22.3 || .452 || .000 || .604 || 5.7 || 0.5 || 0.2 || 1.7 || 1.5 || 5.8\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| 