[[Panchayati raj (India)]]\n| governing_body          = [[Gram panchayat]]\n| website                 = {{URL|kapurthala.gov.in}}\n| footnotes               =\n}}\n'''Bhanoki''' is a village in Tehsil [[Phagwara]], [[Kapurthala district]], in [[Punjab (India)|Punjab]], India.  It is located {{convert|3|km}} away from sub-district headquarter Phagwara and 50&nbsp;km away from district headquarter [[Kapurthala]].  The village is [[Administration (government)|administrated]] by a [[Sarpanch]], who is an [[elected representative]].\n\n==Transport==\nPhagwara Junction [[Railway Station]], Mauli Halt [[Railway Station]] are the very nearby railway stations to Bhanoki however, Jalandhar City Rail Way station is 23&nbsp;km away from the village.  The village is 117&nbsp;km away from [[Sri Guru Ram Dass Jee International Airport]] in [[Amritsar]] and the another nearest airport is [[Sahnewal Airport]]  in [[Ludhiana]] which is located 37&nbsp;km away from the village.shaminder\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n<!-- Please Note: Do not add any promotional information on this page. Any promotional/spam Links or any other information added will be removed immediately -->Before the early 1990s Bhanoki had often sports activities such as annual kabbadi tournaments wrestlings (chhingh) cricket football etc. Oh mazze hor hi si jadon bhaari bhohar te baith ke taash khelni.. Gulli danda... Bander killa Haha.. Jhang planga... Yaar lithe gayiiaan eh khela...\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.censusindia.gov.in/2011census/Listofvillagesandtowns.aspx  Villages in Kapurthala]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20160915101605/http://punjabdata.com/Villages/Villages-In-Kapurthala-Tehsil-In-Kapurthala-District.html Kapurthala Villages List]\n\n{{Kapurthala district |state=collapsed}}\n\n[[Category:Villages in Kapurthala district]]\n\n\n{{Kapurthala-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{unreferenced|date=June 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=April 2018}}\n{{Infobo