019-04-25}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:50px;\" |Year\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:150px;\" |Magazine\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:400px;\" |Article(s)\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:220px;\" |Author(s)\n!Editor\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |1970\n| scope=\"row\" |[[Redbook]]\n|\"Tonight at 9:36\" <br />\"Troubadour\" <br />\"The Magic Mama\"\n| Alfred Gillespie <br />Rick Sterry <br />Lucille Clifton\n|Sey Chassler, Editor in Chief\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |1971\n| scope=\"row\" |''[[Esquire (magazine)|Esquire]]''\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |1972\n| scope=\"row\" |''[[Mademoiselle (magazine)|Mademoiselle]]''\n|\"A Most Incredible Meal\"\n|William Kotzwinkle\n|\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |1973\n| scope=\"row\" |''[[The Atlantic]]''\n|\"Enormous Changes at the Last Minute\"\n|Grace Paley\n|\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |1974\n| scope=\"row\" |''[[The New Yorker]]''\n|\"A Bad Baby\" <br />\"A Story in an Almost Classical Mode\" <br />\"Burial\"\n|Roberta Silman <br />Harold Brodkey <br />Larry Woiwode\n|William Shawn, Editor\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |1975\n| scope=\"row\" |[[Redbook]]\n|\"Swimmer in the Secret Sea\"\n|William Kotzwinkle\n|Sey Chassler, Editor in Chief\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |1976\n| scope=\"row\" |[[Essence (magazine)|Essence]]\n|\"Isom\"\n|Hortense Spillers\n|Marcia Anne Gillespie, Editor in Chief\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |1977\n| scope=\"row\" |''[[Mother Jones (magazine)|Mother Jones]]'''\n|\"Peking! Peking!\"\n|Li-li Ch\u2019en\n|Jeffrey Klein, Editor\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |1978\n| scope=\"row\" |''[[The New Yorker]]''\n|\"In the Miro District\" <br />\"Potter\" <br />\"The Kugelmass Episode\"\n|Peter Taylor <br />Mavis Gallant <br />Woody Allen\n|William Shawn, Editor\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |1979\n| scope=\"row\" |''[[The Atlantic]]''\n|\"Oh, Joseph, I\u2019m So Tired\"\n|Richard Yates\n|Robert Manning, Editor\n|-\n| align=\"center\" |1980\n| scope=\"row\" |''[[Antaeus (magazine)|Antae